workout_details.description: Running is a cardiovascular exercise that improves heart health, burns calories, and strengthens lower body muscles. A 45-minute session at a moderate pace can burn approximately 405 calories, depending on weight and speed.

A chest day at the gym typically involves exercises like bench press, dumbbell flys, push-ups, and cable crossovers. This workout targets the pectoralis major and minor muscles, as well as the triceps and shoulders. The estimated calorie burn is based on a moderate to high intensity level, considering the duration and typical effort involved in chest exercises.
A gentle, leisurely walk at a slow pace, suitable for beginners or as a warm-up/cool-down activity.
